Waste Classification using Transfer Learning Method¶

Australia generates tens of million tonnes of waste every year, and the figure is continuously increasing day by day. Reduce and recycle waste can help to keep the environment clean while recycling in a wrong bin may lead to severe damage to the recycle machine or health issues to the working staff. In this project, we will develop a deep learning model (CNN - Keras/Transfer Learning) which can help to raise people's awareness and skills in recycling.¶
In this project, we are using 6283 images for training (including 10% for validation) and 1272 images for testing, both are belonging to 6 classes. Our target classes are the 6 types of waste materials which are "paper", "cardboard", "glass", "metal", "plastic", and "trash". Trash are the waste which are not for recycle, while the other five materials can be recycled accordingly. To build the classification model that can correctly sort out different types of wastes, we need each image has a corresponding label that can illustrate the correct prediction as the output.¶

In [ ]:
# Feed to a dense top
def make_model():
  model = models.Sequential()
  model.add(base_model)
  model.add(layers.Flatten())
  model.add(layers.Dense(256, activation = "relu"))
  model.add(layers.Dropout(0.45))
  model.add(layers.Dense(6, activation = "softmax"))

  model.compile(optimizer = optimizers.RMSprop(lr = 2e-5),
                loss = "sparse_categorical_crossentropy",
                metrics = ["accuracy"])

  return model

model = make_model()
model.summary()

Build an input pipeline for data augmentation¶

In [ ]:
IMAGE_SIZE = 150
def augment(image,label):
  image = tf.image.rot90(image)
  image = tf.image.random_flip_left_right(image)
  image = tf.image.resize(image, (IMAGE_SIZE, IMAGE_SIZE))
  image = tf.image.adjust_saturation(image, 3)
  image = tf.image.adjust_brightness(image, 0.4)

  return image, label
In [ ]:
train_dataset = train_dataset.map(augment)
val_dataset = val_dataset.map(augment)

import gradio as gr

def waste_classification(input_img):
  # img = tf.keras.preprocessing.image.load_img(input_img, target_size=(150, 150))
  # input_img = input.reshape(150, 150)
  img_array = tf.keras.preprocessing.image.img_to_array(input_img)
  img_array = tf.expand_dims(img_array, 0)

  pred_result = model_ft.predict(img_array)
  return classes[np.argmax(pred_result)]

title = "Waste Classification Aid"
description = "Please upload your photo here and click submit."
article = "Recycle wastes include PAPER, CARDBOARD, METAL, HARD PLASTIC, and GLASS. Other trash are not for recycle."

inputs = gr.inputs.Image(shape = (150, 150))
outputs = gr.outputs.Label(num_top_classes = 6)
gr.Interface(fn = waste_classification, inputs = inputs, outputs = outputs,
             title = title, description = description, article = article).launch()
